node.text:
What’s in your shaker???

Honestly had one of the best upper body workouts I’ve had in months. Didn’t feel distracted, I felt energetic and motivated. Obviously gaining weight has its ups and downs (more so mentally than physically) but combine SUFFICIENT food (fuel) with the right supplements (based on YOUR needs and goals) and the right training plan, you WILL be surprised at how well your body will respond.

I personally have made some MAJOR changes when it comes to my training (intensity especially) and also have been worrying less about how “lean” I look and more on fuelling my body for success and optimal training this off season.

As for supplements, I’ve been posting a lot about @jacked_factory hydrosurge and intrasurge. Keeping your body hydrated is JUST AS important as fuelling it for success (if not more).

 I drink 2-3 scoops of hydrosurge each day to help me get those extra electrolytes in and keep my muscles and body hydrated.

I take intrasurge during my work outs to help keep energy consistent, increase focus, to assist my muscles with recovery and enhance my overall performance.

I hope everyone is enjoying their first week back in the gym!! If you have any questions about the products I mentioned above be sure to check out the JF website (they have big sales on!!!!) or shoot me a DM!!

Oh & @morganmac.bodybuilding, @morganverafitness and other athletes are always sharing very informative info on these products so check it out 👏🏻💪🏻
